Description: Fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows one side with one coil of basketry and a further side with less clear impressions. The front shows finger impressions and a very small part of a seal-impression. Visible is a circumferential line and an upright cobra facing to the right.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
